  "is_vocab": false,
  "stimulus_html": "Because of their conjugation, azo dyes are highly colored compounds and the major artificial color source for textiles and food. Azo dyes are produced by the reaction of aryl diazonium salts with a second aromatic compound. In the product, the aromatic rings are linked by a diazo bridge ( – N=N – ). From the reactants provided, propose a structure for each azo dye and draw the electron-pushing mechanism.",
